      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p>The papers of Johann Carl Philipp von Krafft, Hessian army officer and
		  surveyor, were given to the Library of Congress by Carroll B. Cox, Elizabeth
		  Jane Cox Reed, and the Cox family in 1994.</p>
